to a compelling account of the impact that mobility has had on job functions, working conditions, and personal lives. Mobile Hollywood captures how an expanded geography of production not only intensifies the often invisible pressures that production workers now face but also stretches the parameters of screen-media labor far beyond craftwork and creativity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture industryxEmployeesxSocial conditions. 0aMotion picturesxProduction and directionzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520399013zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520399013zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520399013/original  a978-3-11-079135-8 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA